Happy Birthday Eq'ers!<BR><BR>

Today, EQ turns TWO years old. It is hard to believe that the game is still going so strong and continues to increase in popularity daily. To mark this occassion, I have posted a special anniversery update to our site!<BR><BR>

Foremost in the update is a special <A HREF="stories/unique.phtml">article</A> I have written about EQ past and present. I hope I have captured how EverQuest has been a part of my life for well over 2 years now, and how, even though I don't play regularily anymore, I still interact in the community of EQ, and take great pleasure in helping keep this site running for all you players and fans.</FONT><BR><BR>


<A HREF="main.phtml"><B>Polls:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="arial">
Here are the results from the poll that has been up for the past month and a bit. The question was "<I>If there are no more add-ons to EQ, about how much longer will you play it?</I>". It's quite obvious most of you are still totally addicted to this game, hehe.
</FONT><BR><BR>

